Note:
OPENAPI - OpenAPI 3.1 Specification Primitive (Tier 1)

Implements the OpenAPI 3.1 specification (https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.1.0)
as a typed AST. The parser accepts a JSON-serialized OpenAPI document
(or the JSON form of a YAML document, which the higher-layer YAML module
converts to JSON for us) and produces an OpenApiSpec value.

Top-level structure:
  OpenApiSpec   { openapi, info, servers, paths, components, security,
                  tags, externalDocs }
  Info          { title, version, description, termsOfService, contact,
                  license, summary }
  Contact       { name, url, email }
  License       { name, url, identifier }
  ExternalDocs  { description, url }
  Tag           { name, description, externalDocs }
  PathItem      { get, put, post, delete, options, head, patch, trace,
                  parameters, summary }
  Operation     { operationId, parameters, requestBody, responses,
                  security, tags, description, summary, deprecated }
  Parameter     { name, in (query/header/path/cookie), schema, required,
                  description, style }
  Components    { schemas, responses, parameters, examples,
                  requestBodies, headers, securitySchemes, links,
                  callbacks, pathItems }

Layout (OpenApiSpec, 64 bytes):
  offset  0 : openapi_version  (8 bytes, String pointer e.g. "3.1.0")
  offset  8 : info             (8 bytes, Info pointer)
  offset 16 : servers          (8 bytes, List<Server>)
  offset 24 : paths            (8 bytes, Dictionary<String, PathItem>)
  offset 32 : components       (8 bytes, Components pointer or 0)
  offset 40 : security         (8 bytes, List<SecurityRequirement> or 0)
  offset 48 : tags             (8 bytes, List<Tag> or 0)
  offset 56 : external_docs    (8 bytes, ExternalDocs pointer or 0)

Layout (Info, 56 bytes):
  offset  0 : title            (8 bytes, String)
  offset  8 : version          (8 bytes, String)
  offset 16 : description      (8 bytes, String or 0)
  offset 24 : terms_of_service (8 bytes, String or 0)
  offset 32 : contact          (8 bytes, Contact pointer or 0)
  offset 40 : license          (8 bytes, License pointer or 0)
  offset 48 : summary          (8 bytes, String or 0)

Layout (PathItem, 80 bytes): nine slots for HTTP verb operations plus a
shared parameter list.
  offset  0 : get      (8 bytes, Operation pointer or 0)
  offset  8 : put      (8 bytes)
  offset 16 : post     (8 bytes)
  offset 24 : delete   (8 bytes)
  offset 32 : options  (8 bytes)
  offset 40 : head     (8 bytes)
  offset 48 : patch    (8 bytes)
  offset 56 : trace    (8 bytes)
  offset 64 : parameters (8 bytes, List<Parameter>)
  offset 72 : summary   (8 bytes, String or 0)

Layout (Operation, 72 bytes):
  offset  0 : operation_id (8 bytes, String or 0)
  offset  8 : parameters   (8 bytes, List<Parameter>)
  offset 16 : request_body (8 bytes, RequestBody pointer or 0)
  offset 24 : responses    (8 bytes, Dictionary<String, Response>)
  offset 32 : security     (8 bytes, List<SecurityRequirement> or 0)
  offset 40 : tags         (8 bytes, List<String> or 0)
  offset 48 : description  (8 bytes, String or 0)
  offset 56 : summary      (8 bytes, String or 0)
  offset 64 : deprecated   (8 bytes, 0 or 1)

Layout (Parameter, 48 bytes):
  offset  0 : name        (8 bytes, String)
  offset  8 : location    (8 bytes, IN_* constant)
  offset 16 : schema      (8 bytes, SchemaNode pointer)
  offset 24 : required    (8 bytes, 0 or 1)
  offset 32 : description (8 bytes, String or 0)
  offset 40 : style       (8 bytes, String or 0)

Layout (Tag, 24 bytes):
  offset  0 : name           (8 bytes, String)
  offset  8 : description    (8 bytes, String or 0)
  offset 16 : external_docs  (8 bytes, ExternalDocs pointer or 0)

Layout (Contact, 24 bytes):
  offset  0 : name   (8 bytes, String or 0)
  offset  8 : url    (8 bytes, String or 0)
  offset 16 : email  (8 bytes, String or 0)

Layout (License, 24 bytes):
  offset  0 : name        (8 bytes, String)
  offset  8 : url         (8 bytes, String or 0)
  offset 16 : identifier  (8 bytes, String or 0)

Layout (ExternalDocs, 16 bytes):
  offset  0 : description  (8 bytes, String or 0)
  offset  8 : url          (8 bytes, String)

Layout (Components, 80 bytes): ten name-keyed dictionaries holding each
component category. Each slot is a Dictionary<String, ...> pointer or 0
when the category has no entries.
  offset  0 : schemas          (8 bytes, Dictionary<String, SchemaNode>)
  offset  8 : responses        (8 bytes, Dictionary<String, SchemaNode>)
  offset 16 : parameters       (8 bytes, Dictionary<String, Parameter>)
  offset 24 : examples         (8 bytes, Dictionary<String, ConfigValue>)
  offset 32 : request_bodies   (8 bytes, Dictionary<String, ConfigValue>)
  offset 40 : headers          (8 bytes, Dictionary<String, Parameter>)
  offset 48 : security_schemes (8 bytes, Dictionary<String, ConfigValue>)
  offset 56 : links            (8 bytes, Dictionary<String, ConfigValue>)
  offset 64 : callbacks        (8 bytes, Dictionary<String, ConfigValue>)
  offset 72 : path_items       (8 bytes, Dictionary<String, PathItem>)

SecurityRequirement values are represented as Dictionary<String, List<String>>
mapping scheme-name to list of OAuth2 scopes (or an empty list for API
keys / HTTP auth). The top-level "security" slot holds a List of these
dictionaries; an Operation's "security" slot holds the same shape and
overrides the top-level.

References:
  - OpenAPI 3.1.0 specification  https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.1.0
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrim
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dict
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/string_builder.runa" as SB
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/config/config.runa" as Cfg
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/schema/schema.runa" as Schema
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/schema/json_schema.runa" as JsonSchema

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTANTS
Note: ============================================================================

Let OPENAPI_SPEC_SIZE be 64
Let INFO_SIZE be 56
Let PATH_ITEM_SIZE be 80
Let OPERATION_SIZE be 72
Let PARAMETER_SIZE be 48
Let TAG_SIZE be 24
Let CONTACT_SIZE be 24
Let LICENSE_SIZE be 24
Let EXTERNAL_DOCS_SIZE be 16
Let COMPONENTS_SIZE be 80

Note: Parameter "in" locations per OAS 3.1 sec.4.8.13.
Let IN_QUERY be 1
Let IN_HEADER be 2
Let IN_PATH be 3
Let IN_COOKIE be 4

Note: HTTP verbs.
Let VERB_GET be 1
Let VERB_PUT be 2
Let VERB_POST be 3
Let VERB_DELETE be 4
Let VERB_OPTIONS be 5
Let VERB_HEAD be 6
Let VERB_PATCH be 7
Let VERB_TRACE be 8

Note: ============================================================================
Note: PARAMETER
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Allocate a Parameter record.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 48 bytes; duplicate name; store fields.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|name|). Space: O(|name|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure or null name.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "parameter_create" takes name as Integer, location as Integer, schema_node as Integer, required as Integer returns Integer:
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nm be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with name
    If nm is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let p be proc allocate from Layout with PARAMETER_SIZE
    If p is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with nm
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with p, 0, nm
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with p, 8, location
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with p, 16, schema_node
    Let r be 0
    If required is not equal to 0:
        Set r to 1
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with p, 24, r
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with p, 32, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with p, 40, 0
    Return p
End Process

@Reasoning
Free a Parameter and its owned strings/schema.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Deallocate name, description, style, then schema_destroy on the child.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(s) where s is schema subtree size.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Safe on null.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "parameter_destroy" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nm be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p, 0
    If nm is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with nm
    End If
    Let sch be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p, 16
    If sch is not equal to 0:
        proc schema_destroy from Schema with sch
    End If
    Let desc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p, 32
    If desc is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with desc
    End If
    Let sty be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p, 40
    If sty is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with sty
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with p
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Parameter accessor: name.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "parameter_name" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Parameter accessor: location (IN_*).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 8.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "parameter_location" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p, 8
End Process

@Reasoning
Parameter accessor: schema (SchemaNode).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 16.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "parameter_schema" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p, 16
End Process

@Reasoning
Parameter accessor: required flag.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 24.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "parameter_required" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p, 24
End Process

@Reasoning
Parameter accessor: description (optional human-readable docstring).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 32.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input or absent description.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "parameter_description" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p, 32
End Process

@Reasoning
Set the parameter's description (duplicated). Frees any prior value.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Free prior; duplicate new; store at offset 32.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|d|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null parameter.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "parameter_set_description" takes p as Integer, d as Integer returns Integer:
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let prior be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p, 32
    If prior is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with prior
    End If
    Let dup be 0
    If d is not equal to 0:
        Set dup to proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with d
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with p, 32, dup
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: EXTERNAL DOCS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Allocate an ExternalDocs record with required url and optional description.
The url is duplicated so the caller may free its copy. Mirrors OAS 3.1
section 4.8.11.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 16 bytes; duplicate description (if any) and url.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|description|+|url|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null url or allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "external_docs_create" takes description as Integer, url as Integer returns Integer:
    If url is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let dup_url be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with url
    If dup_url is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let dup_desc be 0
    If description is not equal to 0:
        Set dup_desc to proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with description
        If dup_desc is equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with dup_url
            Return 0
        End If
    End If
    Let ed be proc allocate from Layout with EXTERNAL_DOCS_SIZE
    If ed is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with dup_url
        If dup_desc is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with dup_desc
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ed, 0, dup_desc
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ed, 8, dup_url
    Return ed
End Process

@Reasoning
Free an ExternalDocs record and its owned strings.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Free description, url, then the record itself.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Safe on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "external_docs_destroy" takes ed as Integer returns Integer:
    If ed is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let desc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ed, 0
    If desc is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with desc
    End If
    Let url be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ed, 8
    If url is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with url
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with ed
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Read the ExternalDocs description.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "external_docs_description" takes ed as Integer returns Integer:
    If ed is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ed, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Read the ExternalDocs url.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 8.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "external_docs_url" takes ed as Integer returns Integer:
    If ed is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ed, 8
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONTACT
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Allocate a Contact record with optional name, url, and email. Mirrors
OAS 3.1 section 4.8.3.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 24 bytes; duplicate each non-null argument string.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|name|+|url|+|email|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "contact_create" takes name as Integer, url as Integer, email as Integer returns Integer:
    Let dn be 0
    If name is not equal to 0:
        Set dn to proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with name
        If dn is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If
    Let du be 0
    If url is not equal to 0:
        Set du to proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with url
        If du is equal to 0:
            If dn is not equal to 0:
                proc deallocate from Layout with dn
            End If
            Return 0
        End If
    End If
    Let de be 0
    If email is not equal to 0:
        Set de to proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with email
        If de is equal to 0:
            If dn is not equal to 0:
                proc deallocate from Layout with dn
            End If
            If du is not equal to 0:
                proc deallocate from Layout with du
            End If
            Return 0
        End If
    End If
    Let c be proc allocate from Layout with CONTACT_SIZE
    If c is equal to 0:
        If dn is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with dn
        End If
        If du is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with du
        End If
        If de is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with de
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 0, dn
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 8, du
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 16, de
    Return c
End Process

@Reasoning
Free a Contact record and its owned strings.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk three slots; free each non-zero; deallocate the record.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Safe on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "contact_destroy" takes c as Integer returns Integer:
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than 3:
        Let s be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c, i multiplied by 8
        If s is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with s
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc deallocate from Layout with c
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Read the Contact name.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "contact_name" takes c as Integer returns Integer:
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Read the Contact url.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 8.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "contact_url" takes c as Integer returns Integer:
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c, 8
End Process

@Reasoning
Read the Contact email.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 16.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "contact_email" takes c as Integer returns Integer:
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c, 16
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: LICENSE
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Allocate a License record. The name field is required by OAS 3.1
section 4.8.4. url and identifier are optional and mutually exclusive at
the spec level; this constructor accepts both and the validator enforces
the mutual exclusion.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 24 bytes; duplicate name (mandatory), url, identifier.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|name|+|url|+|identifier|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null name or allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "license_create" takes name as Integer, url as Integer, identifier as Integer returns Integer:
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let dn be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with name
    If dn is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let du be 0
    If url is not equal to 0:
        Set du to proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with url
        If du is equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with dn
            Return 0
        End If
    End If
    Let di be 0
    If identifier is not equal to 0:
        Set di to proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with identifier
        If di is equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with dn
            If du is not equal to 0:
                proc deallocate from Layout with du
            End If
            Return 0
        End If
    End If
    Let l be proc allocate from Layout with LICENSE_SIZE
    If l is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with dn
        If du is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with du
        End If
        If di is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with di
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with l, 0, dn
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with l, 8, du
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with l, 16, di
    Return l
End Process

@Reasoning
Free a License record and its owned strings.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk three slots; free each non-zero; deallocate the record.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Safe on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "license_destroy" takes l as Integer returns Integer:
    If l is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than 3:
        Let s be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with l, i multiplied by 8
        If s is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with s
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc deallocate from Layout with l
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Read the License name (mandatory).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "license_name" takes l as Integer returns Integer:
    If l is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with l, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Read the License url (optional).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 8.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input or absent url.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "license_url" takes l as Integer returns Integer:
    If l is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with l, 8
End Process

@Reasoning
Read the License SPDX identifier (optional).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 16.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input or absent identifier.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "license_identifier" takes l as Integer returns Integer:
    If l is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with l, 16
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TAG
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Allocate a Tag record with required name, optional description, and
optional ExternalDocs link. Mirrors OAS 3.1 section 4.8.22.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 24 bytes; duplicate name; duplicate description if present;
adopt the ExternalDocs pointer ownership (caller relinquishes).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|name|+|description|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null name or allocation failure. On failure the supplied
external_docs is NOT destroyed - the caller retains ownership in that
case.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "tag_create" takes name as Integer, description as Integer, external_docs as Integer returns Integer:
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let dn be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with name
    If dn is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let dd be 0
    If description is not equal to 0:
        Set dd to proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with description
        If dd is equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with dn
            Return 0
        End If
    End If
    Let t be proc allocate from Layout with TAG_SIZE
    If t is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with dn
        If dd is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with dd
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with t, 0, dn
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with t, 8, dd
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with t, 16, external_docs
    Return t
End Process

@Reasoning
Free a Tag record and every owned child (name, description, externalDocs).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Free strings then destroy external_docs subtree.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Safe on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "tag_destroy" takes t as Integer returns Integer:
    If t is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nm be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with t, 0
    If nm is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with nm
    End If
    Let dsc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with t, 8
    If dsc is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with dsc
    End If
    Let ed be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with t, 16
    If ed is not equal to 0:
        proc external_docs_destroy with ed
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with t
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Read the Tag name.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
