Note: ============================================================================
Note: COMPONENTS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Allocate a Components record with all ten category dictionaries
pre-created. Mirrors OAS 3.1 section 4.8.7. Each dictionary is a
String -> object map; the destructor knows how to free each category
correctly because each occupies a fixed slot offset.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 80 bytes; create ten dictionaries; on partial failure roll
back any dictionaries already created.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "components_create" returns Integer:
    Let c be proc allocate from Layout with COMPONENTS_SIZE
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than 10:
        Let d be proc create from Dict
        If d is equal to 0:
            Let j be 0
            While j is less than i:
                Let prior be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c, j multiplied by 8
                If prior is not equal to 0:
                    proc destroy from Dict with prior
                End If
                Set j to j plus 1
            End While
            proc deallocate from Layout with c
            Return 0
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, i multiplied by 8, d
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return c
End Process

@Reasoning
Free a Components record and every owned object in every category.
Category-specific destructors are invoked based on slot offset:
  - offsets 0/8: SchemaNode entries -> schema_destroy
  - offsets 16/40: Parameter entries -> parameter_destroy
  - offsets 24/32/48/56/64: ConfigValue entries -> config_value_destroy
  - offset 72: PathItem entries -> path_item_destroy
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
For each of the ten slots, walk the dictionary's keys; for each (key,value)
look up the value and invoke the slot-appropriate destructor. Then
list_destroy the keys list, destroy the dictionary itself, and finally
deallocate the Components record.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) where n is total entries across all categories.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Safe on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "components_destroy" takes c as Integer returns Integer:
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let slot be 0
    While slot is less than 10:
        Let d be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c, slot multiplied by 8
        If d is not equal to 0:
            Let ks be proc keys from Dict with d
            If ks is not equal to 0:
                Let kc be proc list_length from List with ks
                Let i be 0
                While i is less than kc:
                    Let key be proc list_get from List with ks, i
                    Let val be proc get from Dict with d, key
                    If val is not equal to 0:
                        If slot is equal to 0:
                            proc schema_destroy from Schema with val
                        End If
                        If slot is equal to 1:
                            proc schema_destroy from Schema with val
                        End If
                        If slot is equal to 2:
                            proc parameter_destroy with val
                        End If
                        If slot is equal to 3:
                            proc config_value_destroy from Cfg with val
                        End If
                        If slot is equal to 4:
                            proc config_value_destroy from Cfg with val
                        End If
                        If slot is equal to 5:
                            proc parameter_destroy with val
                        End If
                        If slot is equal to 6:
                            proc config_value_destroy from Cfg with val
                        End If
                        If slot is equal to 7:
                            proc config_value_destroy from Cfg with val
                        End If
                        If slot is equal to 8:
                            proc config_value_destroy from Cfg with val
                        End If
                        If slot is equal to 9:
                            proc path_item_destroy with val
                        End If
                    End If
                    Set i to i plus 1
                End While
                proc list_destroy from List with ks
            End If
            proc destroy from Dict with d
        End If
        Set slot to slot plus 1
    End While
    proc deallocate from Layout with c
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Components accessor: schemas dictionary.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

