Note: ============================================================================
Note: SECURITY REQUIREMENT
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
A SecurityRequirement is a Dictionary<String, List<String>> mapping a
security scheme name to the list of OAuth2 scope strings (or an empty
list when no scopes apply). Provides allocate/destroy helpers so the
ownership story is symmetric with the other record types.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Create the underlying dictionary; the destructor walks every entry and
destroys the scope list.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "security_requirement_create" returns Integer:
    Return proc create from Dict
End Process

@Reasoning
Free a SecurityRequirement and every owned scope list (and its scope
strings).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk the dictionary's keys; for each scheme name look up the scope
list; walk the list freeing each scope string; destroy the list; finally
destroy the dictionary.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(s) where s is total scopes across schemes.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Safe on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "security_requirement_destroy" takes sr as Integer returns Integer:
    If sr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ks be proc keys from Dict with sr
    If ks is not equal to 0:
        Let kc be proc list_length from List with ks
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than kc:
            Let key be proc list_get from List with ks, i
            Let scopes be proc get from Dict with sr, key
            If scopes is not equal to 0:
                Let sc be proc list_length from List with scopes
                Let j be 0
                While j is less than sc:
                    Let sv be proc list_get from List with scopes, j
                    If sv is not equal to 0:
                        proc deallocate from Layout with sv
                    End If
                    Set j to j plus 1
                End While
                proc list_destroy from List with scopes
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with ks
    End If
    proc destroy from Dict with sr
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: OPERATION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Allocate an Operation with empty parameter list and response dict.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 72 bytes; pre-create the parameters list and responses dict.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "operation_create" returns Integer:
    Let op be proc allocate from Layout with OPERATION_SIZE
    If op is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let params be proc list_create from List
    Let resp be proc create from Dict
    If params is equal to 0:
        If resp is not equal to 0:
            proc destroy from Dict with resp
        End If
        proc deallocate from Layout with op
        Return 0
    End If
    If resp is equal to 0:
        proc list_destroy from List with params
        proc deallocate from Layout with op
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with op, 0, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with op, 8, params
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with op, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with op, 24, resp
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with op, 32, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with op, 40, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with op, 48, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with op, 56, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with op, 64, 0
    Return op
End Process

@Reasoning
Free an Operation and every owned subordinate value.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Deallocate operationId, description, summary; recursively destroy each
parameter, response (which we store as SchemaNode pointer for simplicity).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over owned subtrees.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Safe on null.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "operation_destroy" takes op as Integer returns Integer:
    If op is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let oid be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with op, 0
    If oid is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with oid
    End If
    Let params be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with op, 8
    If params is not equal to 0:
        Let pc be proc list_length from List with params
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than pc:
            Let p be proc list_get from List with params, i
            If p is not equal to 0:
                proc parameter_destroy with p
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with params
    End If
    Let rb be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with op, 16
    If rb is not equal to 0:
        proc config_value_destroy from Cfg with rb
    End If
    Let resp be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with op, 24
    If resp is not equal to 0:
        Let rk be proc keys from Dict with resp
        If rk is not equal to 0:
            Let rc be proc list_length from List with rk
            Let j be 0
            While j is less than rc:
                Let key be proc list_get from List with rk, j
                Let val be proc get from Dict with resp, key
                If val is not equal to 0:
                    proc schema_destroy from Schema with val
                End If
                Set j to j plus 1
            End While
            proc list_destroy from List with rk
        End If
        proc destroy from Dict with resp
    End If
    Let sec be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with op, 32
    If sec is not equal to 0:
        Let scc be proc list_length from List with sec
        Let si be 0
        While si is less than scc:
            Let sr be proc list_get from List with sec, si
            If sr is not equal to 0:
                proc security_requirement_destroy with sr
            End If
            Set si to si plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with sec
    End If
    Let tags be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with op, 40
    If tags is not equal to 0:
        Let tc be proc list_length from List with tags
        Let k be 0
        While k is less than tc:
            Let t be proc list_get from List with tags, k
            If t is not equal to 0:
                proc deallocate from Layout with t
            End If
            Set k to k plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with tags
    End If
    Let desc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with op, 48
    If desc is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with desc
    End If
    Let summ be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with op, 56
    If summ is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with summ
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with op
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Set the operation's operationId (duplicated).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Free prior; duplicate new.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|id|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null op.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "operation_set_id" takes op as Integer, id as Integer returns Integer:
    If op is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let prior be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with op, 0
    If prior is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with prior
    End If
    Let dup be 0
    If id is not equal to 0:
        Set dup to proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with id
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with op, 0, dup
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Append a Parameter to the operation. Operation assumes ownership.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
list_push.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: amortized O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null op or param.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "operation_add_parameter" takes op as Integer, param as Integer returns Integer:
    If op is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If param is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let plist be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with op, 8
    If plist is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc list_push from List with plist, param
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Add a response schema keyed by status code (e.g. "200", "404", "default").
The schema is the response body schema; the operation assumes ownership.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Set in the dict. Prior value is destroyed.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: amortized O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null op or key.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "operation_add_response" takes op as Integer, status_code as Integer, response_schema as Integer returns Integer:
    If op is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If status_code is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let rdict be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with op, 24
    If rdict is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let prior be proc get from Dict with rdict, status_code
    If prior is not equal to 0:
        proc schema_destroy from Schema with prior
    End If
    proc set from Dict with rdict, status_code, response_schema
    Return 1
End Process

