Note: ============================================================================
Note: PATH ITEM
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Allocate an empty PathItem.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 80 bytes; create the shared-parameter list.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "path_item_create" returns Integer:
    Let pi be proc allocate from Layout with PATH_ITEM_SIZE
    If pi is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let params be proc list_create from List
    If params is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with pi
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than 8:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with pi, i multiplied by 8, 0
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with pi, 64, params
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with pi, 72, 0
    Return pi
End Process

@Reasoning
Free a PathItem and all stored operations.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
For each of the 8 verb slots, if non-zero, operation_destroy. Then walk
shared parameters and free.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over owned subtrees.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Safe on null.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "path_item_destroy" takes pi as Integer returns Integer:
    If pi is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let v be 0
    While v is less than 8:
        Let op be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with pi, v multiplied by 8
        If op is not equal to 0:
            proc operation_destroy with op
        End If
        Set v to v plus 1
    End While
    Let params be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with pi, 64
    If params is not equal to 0:
        Let pc be proc list_length from List with params
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than pc:
            Let p be proc list_get from List with params, i
            If p is not equal to 0:
                proc parameter_destroy with p
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with params
    End If
    Let summary be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with pi, 72
    If summary is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with summary
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with pi
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Bind an operation to a verb slot. Prior occupant is destroyed.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Translate verb to slot offset; free prior; store new.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(d) where d is prior subtree.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on invalid verb or null pi/op.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "path_item_set_operation" takes pi as Integer, verb as Integer, op as Integer returns Integer:
    If pi is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If verb is less than 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    If verb is greater than 8:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let off be (verb minus 1) multiplied by 8
    Let prior be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with pi, off
    If prior is not equal to 0:
        proc operation_destroy with prior
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with pi, off, op
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Retrieve the operation at a verb slot.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load slot byte offset.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on invalid verb or null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "path_item_get_operation" takes pi as Integer, verb as Integer returns Integer:
    If pi is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If verb is less than 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    If verb is greater than 8:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let off be (verb minus 1) multiplied by 8
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with pi, off
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: INFO
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Allocate an Info record with required title and version.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 56 bytes; duplicate title+version; zero optional slots.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|title|+|version|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure or null arguments.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "info_create" takes title as Integer, version as Integer returns Integer:
    If title is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If version is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let t be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with title
    If t is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let v be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with version
    If v is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with t
        Return 0
    End If
    Let info be proc allocate from Layout with INFO_SIZE
    If info is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with t
        proc deallocate from Layout with v
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with info, 0, t
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with info, 8, v
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with info, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with info, 24, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with info, 32, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with info, 40, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with info, 48, 0
    Return info
End Process

@Reasoning
Free an Info record and its owned strings.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Free each non-zero slot.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Safe on null.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "info_destroy" takes info as Integer returns Integer:
    If info is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let title be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with info, 0
    If title is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with title
    End If
    Let version be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with info, 8
    If version is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with version
    End If
    Let desc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with info, 16
    If desc is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with desc
    End If
    Let tos be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with info, 24
    If tos is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with tos
    End If
    Let contact be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with info, 32
