Process called "operation_security" takes op as Integer returns Integer:
    If op is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with op, 32
End Process

@Reasoning
Append a SecurityRequirement to the operation's security list. The list
is created lazily on first append. Operation assumes ownership of sr.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
If the security slot is 0, create a list. Then push sr.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: amortized O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null op or sr.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "operation_add_security" takes op as Integer, sr as Integer returns Integer:
    If op is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If sr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let lst be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with op, 32
    If lst is equal to 0:
        Set lst to proc list_create from List
        If lst is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with op, 32, lst
    End If
    proc list_push from List with lst, sr
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Read the operation requestBody. The body is stored as an owned
ConfigValue subtree because OAS 3.1 RequestBody is itself a recursive
record family (description + content -> media-type -> MediaType {schema,
example, examples, encoding}); downstream tooling walks the subtree via
the Cfg module.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 16.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input or absent body.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "operation_request_body" takes op as Integer returns Integer:
    If op is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with op, 16
End Process

@Reasoning
Attach a requestBody ConfigValue subtree. Frees any prior value.
Operation assumes ownership.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Read prior; if non-zero config_value_destroy it; store the new pointer.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) for prior subtree destruction.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null op.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "operation_set_request_body" takes op as Integer, rb as Integer returns Integer:
    If op is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let prior be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with op, 16
    If prior is not equal to 0:
        proc config_value_destroy from Cfg with prior
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with op, 16, rb
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: PARSE HELPERS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Deep-clone a ConfigValue subtree. The OpenAPI parser walks a transient
ConfigValue tree owned by openapi_parse; whenever we need to retain a
subtree past that lifetime (e.g. when stashing a requestBody, example,
security scheme, link, or callback inside an OpenApiSpec / Components
record) we deep-copy through this helper so destruction is unambiguous.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Switch on kind. CV_NULL: emit fresh null. CV_STRING: duplicate the
string (config_value_string itself duplicates so we just pass the
backing pointer). CV_INTEGER / CV_BOOL: read inline value and construct.
CV_FLOAT: round-trip through string form because config.runa does not
expose float storage. CV_LIST: build a new list, recursively clone
each element, install via config_value_list. CV_MAP: build a new
dictionary, recursively clone each (key,value) and install via
config_value_map.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over the source subtree. Space: O(n) for the clone, O(d) on
the call stack.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure at any depth (and frees the partial
clone on failure).
@End Security_Scope
Process called "cv_deep_clone" takes src as Integer returns Integer:
    If src is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let kind be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with src
    If kind is equal to 0:
        Return proc config_value_null from Cfg
    End If
    If kind is equal to 1:
        Let s be proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with src
        If s is equal to 0:
            Return proc config_value_null from Cfg
        End If
        Return proc config_value_string from Cfg with s
    End If
    If kind is equal to 2:
        Let iv be proc config_value_as_integer from Cfg with src
        Return proc config_value_integer from Cfg with iv
    End If
    If kind is equal to 4:
        Let bv be proc config_value_as_bool from Cfg with src
        Return proc config_value_bool from Cfg with bv
    End If
    If kind is equal to 5:
        Let src_lst be proc config_value_as_list from Cfg with src
        Let new_lst be proc list_create from List
        If new_lst is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let n be proc list_length from List with src_lst
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than n:
            Let elem be proc list_get from List with src_lst, i
            Let cloned be proc cv_deep_clone with elem
            If cloned is equal to 0:
                Let nlen be proc list_length from List with new_lst
                Let j be 0
                While j is less than nlen:
                    Let prior be proc list_get from List with new_lst, j
                    If prior is not equal to 0:
                        proc config_value_destroy from Cfg with prior
                    End If
                    Set j to j plus 1
                End While
                proc list_destroy from List with new_lst
                Return 0
            End If
            proc list_push from List with new_lst, cloned
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Let wrapped be proc config_value_list from Cfg with new_lst
        If wrapped is equal to 0:
            Let nlen2 be proc list_length from List with new_lst
            Let j be 0
            While j is less than nlen2:
                Let prior be proc list_get from List with new_lst, j
                If prior is not equal to 0:
                    proc config_value_destroy from Cfg with prior
                End If
                Set j to j plus 1
            End While
            proc list_destroy from List with new_lst
            Return 0
        End If
        Return wrapped
    End If
    If kind is equal to 6:
        Let src_map be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with src
        Let new_map be proc create from Dict
        If new_map is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let ks be proc keys from Dict with src_map
        If ks is not equal to 0:
            Let n2 be proc list_length from List with ks
            Let i2 be 0
            While i2 is less than n2:
                Let key be proc list_get from List with ks, i2
                Let val be proc get from Dict with src_map, key
                Let cloned_val be proc cv_deep_clone with val
                If cloned_val is equal to 0:
                    Let kk be proc keys from Dict with new_map
                    If kk is not equal to 0:
                        Let kkc be proc list_length from List with kk
                        Let kki be 0
                        While kki is less than kkc:
                            Let kkey be proc list_get from List with kk, kki
                            Let kval be proc get from Dict with new_map, kkey
                            If kval is not equal to 0:
                                proc config_value_destroy from Cfg with kval
                            End If
                            Set kki to kki plus 1
                        End While
                        proc list_destroy from List with kk
                    End If
                    proc destroy from Dict with new_map
                    proc list_destroy from List with ks
                    Return 0
                End If
                proc set from Dict with new_map, key, cloned_val
                Set i2 to i2 plus 1
            End While
            proc list_destroy from List with ks
        End If
        Let wrapped_m be proc config_value_map from Cfg with new_map
        If wrapped_m is equal to 0:
            Let kk2 be proc keys from Dict with new_map
            If kk2 is not equal to 0:
                Let kk2c be proc list_length from List with kk2
                Let kk2i be 0
                While kk2i is less than kk2c:
                    Let kk2y be proc list_get from List with kk2, kk2i
                    Let kk2v be proc get from Dict with new_map, kk2y
                    If kk2v is not equal to 0:
                        proc config_value_destroy from Cfg with kk2v
                    End If
                    Set kk2i to kk2i plus 1
                End While
                proc list_destroy from List with kk2
            End If
            proc destroy from Dict with new_map
            Return 0
        End If
        Return wrapped_m
    End If
    Return proc config_value_null from Cfg
End Process

@Reasoning
Read the (kind, string-value) pair from a ConfigValue map entry and
return the duplicated string only when kind == CV_STRING. The returned
pointer is owned by the source ConfigValue, so callers must duplicate
if they intend to keep it past the source's lifetime.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Look up the key; verify kind; return raw string pointer or 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 if key absent or not a string.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "cv_map_string_ref" takes map as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If map is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let entry be proc get from Dict with map, key
    If entry is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let k be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with entry
    If k is not equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with entry
End Process

@Reasoning
Extract optional Contact subtree from an Info ConfigValue map. Builds
a Contact record from {name, url, email} string entries.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Look up "contact" in the info map; verify CV_MAP; read each of the
three string sub-fields; build via contact_create.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|sum of strings|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 if contact entry absent, non-map, or contact_create fails.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "extract_contact" takes info_map as Integer returns Integer:
    Let c_cv be proc get from Dict with info_map, "contact"
    If c_cv is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ck be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with c_cv
    If ck is not equal to 6:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cmap be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with c_cv
    Let name_s be proc cv_map_string_ref with cmap, "name"
    Let url_s be proc cv_map_string_ref with cmap, "url"
    Let email_s be proc cv_map_string_ref with cmap, "email"
    Return proc contact_create with name_s, url_s, email_s
End Process

@Reasoning
Extract optional License subtree from an Info ConfigValue map. Builds
a License record from {name, url, identifier} string entries. OAS 3.1
requires the "name" field if a license block is present.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Look up "license" in the info map; verify CV_MAP; read each string
sub-field; build via license_create (which validates name).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|sum of strings|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 if license entry absent, non-map, missing required name, or
license_create fails.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "extract_license" takes info_map as Integer returns Integer:
    Let l_cv be proc get from Dict with info_map, "license"
    If l_cv is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let lk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with l_cv
    If lk is not equal to 6:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let lmap be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with l_cv
    Let name_s be proc cv_map_string_ref with lmap, "name"
    Let url_s be proc cv_map_string_ref with lmap, "url"
    Let id_s be proc cv_map_string_ref with lmap, "identifier"
    Return proc license_create with name_s, url_s, id_s
End Process

@Reasoning
Extract optional ExternalDocs from a CV_MAP at the given key. Builds
an ExternalDocs record from {description, url}. The "url" field is
required by OAS 3.1; if absent the function returns 0 and the caller
keeps the slot empty.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Look up the key; verify CV_MAP; read description and url; if url
present invoke external_docs_create.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|description|+|url|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 if entry absent, malformed, missing url, or allocation fails.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "extract_external_docs_at" takes parent_map as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    Let ed_cv be proc get from Dict with parent_map, key
    If ed_cv is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ek be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with ed_cv
    If ek is not equal to 6:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let emap be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with ed_cv
    Let url_s be proc cv_map_string_ref with emap, "url"
    If url_s is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let desc_s be proc cv_map_string_ref with emap, "description"
    Return proc external_docs_create with desc_s, url_s
End Process

@Reasoning
Walk the Info CV map and apply description / termsOfService / summary
string fields plus contact / license sub-records to a previously
constructed Info record.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
For each optional scalar string field present in the source map, call
the matching info_set_* setter (which duplicates input). For contact /
license, call extract_contact / extract_license and install via
info_set_contact / info_set_license.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|sum of input fields|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 1 on completion. Missing optional fields are silently skipped.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "populate_info_extras" takes info as Integer, info_map as Integer returns Integer:
    If info is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If info_map is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let desc_s be proc cv_map_string_ref with info_map, "description"
    If desc_s is not equal to 0:
        proc info_set_description with info, desc_s
    End If
    Let tos_s be proc cv_map_string_ref with info_map, "termsOfService"
    If tos_s is not equal to 0:
        proc info_set_terms_of_service with info, tos_s
    End If
    Let summary_s be proc cv_map_string_ref with info_map, "summary"
    If summary_s is not equal to 0:
        proc info_set_summary with info, summary_s
    End If
    Let contact be proc extract_contact with info_map
    If contact is not equal to 0:
        proc info_set_contact with info, contact
    End If
    Let license be proc extract_license with info_map
    If license is not equal to 0:
        proc info_set_license with info, license
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Translate a single SecurityRequirement CV_MAP entry into a
Dictionary<String, List<String>> of (scheme-name -> list-of-scope-strings).
Each scope string is duplicated so the resulting structure owns its
content independently of the source CV tree.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate the requirement dictionary. For each scheme key in the source
map: verify the value is CV_LIST; build a fresh list of duplicated
scope strings; install into the requirement dictionary.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) where n is total scopes across schemes.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure. Malformed source entries (non-list
values, non-string scopes) are skipped silently.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "extract_security_requirement" takes cv as Integer returns Integer:
    If cv is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let k be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with cv
    If k is not equal to 6:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let src_map be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with cv
    Let sr be proc security_requirement_create
    If sr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ks be proc keys from Dict with src_map
    If ks is not equal to 0:
        Let kc be proc list_length from List with ks
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than kc:
            Let scheme be proc list_get from List with ks, i
            Let scopes_cv be proc get from Dict with src_map, scheme
            Let scopes_list be proc list_create from List
            If scopes_list is not equal to 0:
                If scopes_cv is not equal to 0:
                    Let sck be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with scopes_cv
                    If sck is equal to 5:
                        Let src_scopes be proc config_value_as_list from Cfg with scopes_cv
                        Let scn be proc list_length from List with src_scopes
                        Let sci be 0
                        While sci is less than scn:
                            Let scope_cv be proc list_get from List with src_scopes, sci
                            Let scope_kind be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with scope_cv
                            If scope_kind is equal to 1:
                                Let scope_s be proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with scope_cv
                                If scope_s is not equal to 0:
                                    Let dup be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with scope_s
                                    If dup is not equal to 0:
                                        proc list_push from List with scopes_list, dup
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                            Set sci to sci plus 1
                        End While
                    End If
                End If
                proc set from Dict with sr, scheme, scopes_list
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with ks
    End If
    Return sr
End Process

@Reasoning
Walk the top-level "security" array and install one SecurityRequirement
per entry. Spec assumes ownership of each requirement.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Verify the value is a CV_LIST. For each element invoke
extract_security_requirement and openapi_spec_add_security on success.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over total requirements + scopes.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 1 on completion. Returns 0 if spec is null.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "populate_top_level_security" takes spec as Integer, root as Integer returns Integer:
    If spec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sec_cv be proc get from Dict with root, "security"
    If sec_cv is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let sk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with sec_cv
    If sk is not equal to 5:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let sec_list be proc config_value_as_list from Cfg with sec_cv
    Let n be proc list_length from List with sec_list
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than n:
        Let entry be proc list_get from List with sec_list, i
        Let sr be proc extract_security_requirement with entry
        If sr is not equal to 0:
            proc openapi_spec_add_security with spec, sr
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Walk the top-level "tags" array and install one Tag record per entry.
Each Tag captures name (required), description (optional), and an
optional ExternalDocs subobject.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Verify the value is a CV_LIST. For each element verify CV_MAP and
required "name" field, then read description and externalDocs and
build via tag_create.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over total tags.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 1 on completion. Returns 0 if spec is null. Malformed entries
silently skipped.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "populate_top_level_tags" takes spec as Integer, root as Integer returns Integer:
    If spec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tags_cv be proc get from Dict with root, "tags"
    If tags_cv is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let tk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with tags_cv
    If tk is not equal to 5:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let tags_list be proc config_value_as_list from Cfg with tags_cv
    Let n be proc list_length from List with tags_list
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than n:
        Let entry be proc list_get from List with tags_list, i
        Let ek be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with entry
        If ek is equal to 6:
            Let emap be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with entry
            Let name_s be proc cv_map_string_ref with emap, "name"
            If name_s is not equal to 0:
                Let desc_s be proc cv_map_string_ref with emap, "description"
                Let ed be proc extract_external_docs_at with emap, "externalDocs"
                Let tag be proc tag_create with name_s, desc_s, ed
                If tag is not equal to 0:
                    proc openapi_spec_add_tag with spec, tag
                Otherwise:
                    If ed is not equal to 0:
                        proc external_docs_destroy with ed
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Walk the top-level "externalDocs" subobject and install an
ExternalDocs record on the spec.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Delegate to extract_external_docs_at; on success attach via
openapi_spec_set_external_docs.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|description|+|url|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 1 on completion regardless of whether the field was present.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "populate_top_level_external_docs" takes spec as Integer, root as Integer returns Integer:
    If spec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ed be proc extract_external_docs_at with root, "externalDocs"
    If ed is not equal to 0:
        proc openapi_spec_set_external_docs with spec, ed
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper that populates one category dictionary inside a Components
record. Each entry in the source CV map becomes a (key,value) pair in
the destination dict, with the value passed through the kind-specific
adapter.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
For each key in the source map, verify the value is a CV_MAP, then
invoke the supplied adapter selector. adapter_kind selects:
  0 = schema_destroy / cv_to_schema   (SchemaNode)
  1 = parameter_destroy / build Parameter from {name,in,schema,required,description}
  2 = config_value_destroy / cv_deep_clone (ConfigValue subtree)
  3 = path_item_destroy / path_item_from_cv (PathItem)
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n * size-of-each-entry) over the category.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 1 on completion. Silently skips malformed entries.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "populate_component_category" takes dst_dict as Integer, src_map as Integer, adapter_kind as Integer returns Integer:
    If dst_dict is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If src_map is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let ks be proc keys from Dict with src_map
    If ks is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let n be proc list_length from List with ks
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than n:
        Let key be proc list_get from List with ks, i
        Let val be proc get from Dict with src_map, key
        If val is not equal to 0:
            If adapter_kind is equal to 0:
                Let s be proc cv_to_schema from JsonSchema with val
                If s is not equal to 0:
                    proc set from Dict with dst_dict, key, s
                End If
            End If
            If adapter_kind is equal to 1:
                Let pk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with val
                If pk is equal to 6:
                    Let pmap be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with val
                    Let nm_s be proc cv_map_string_ref with pmap, "name"
                    Let in_s be proc cv_map_string_ref with pmap, "in"
                    If nm_s is not equal to 0:
                        If in_s is not equal to 0:
                            Let loc be proc in_name_to_constant with in_s
                            Let psch be 0
                            Let sch_cv be proc get from Dict with pmap, "schema"
                            If sch_cv is not equal to 0:
                                Set psch to proc cv_to_schema from JsonSchema with sch_cv
                            End If
                            Let req_flag be 0
                            Let req_cv be proc get from Dict with pmap, "required"
                            If req_cv is not equal to 0:
                                Let rk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with req_cv
                                If rk is equal to 4:
                                    Set req_flag to proc config_value_as_bool from Cfg with req_cv
                                End If
                            End If
                            Let pdesc_s be proc cv_map_string_ref with pmap, "description"
                            Let param be proc parameter_create with nm_s, loc, psch, req_flag
                            If param is not equal to 0:
                                If pdesc_s is not equal to 0:
                                    proc parameter_set_description with param, pdesc_s
                                End If
                                proc set from Dict with dst_dict, key, param
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
            If adapter_kind is equal to 2:
                Let cloned be proc cv_deep_clone with val
                If cloned is not equal to 0:
                    proc set from Dict with dst_dict, key, cloned
                End If
            End If
            If adapter_kind is equal to 3:
                Let path_item be proc path_item_from_cv with val
                If path_item is not equal to 0:
                    proc set from Dict with dst_dict, key, path_item
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc list_destroy from List with ks
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Build a Components record from the top-level "components" subtree.
Walks ten category dictionaries: schemas, responses, parameters,
examples, requestBodies, headers, securitySchemes, links, callbacks,
pathItems.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate Components. For each category present in the source, walk
the sub-map populating the matching destination dictionary using
populate_component_category with the appropriate adapter kind.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over the total components subtree.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 1 on completion (the components record is installed on the
spec). Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "populate_top_level_components" takes spec as Integer, root as Integer returns Integer:
    If spec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let comp_cv be proc get from Dict with root, "components"
    If comp_cv is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let ck be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with comp_cv
    If ck is not equal to 6:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let cmap be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with comp_cv
    Let components be proc components_create
    If components is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let schemas_cv be proc get from Dict with cmap, "schemas"
    If schemas_cv is not equal to 0:
        Let smk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with schemas_cv
        If smk is equal to 6:
            Let dst be proc components_schemas with components
            Let src be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with schemas_cv
            proc populate_component_category with dst, src, 0
        End If
    End If

    Let resp_cv be proc get from Dict with cmap, "responses"
    If resp_cv is not equal to 0:
        Let rmk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with resp_cv
        If rmk is equal to 6:
            Let dst be proc components_responses with components
            Let src be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with resp_cv
            proc populate_component_category with dst, src, 0
        End If
    End If

    Let params_cv be proc get from Dict with cmap, "parameters"
    If params_cv is not equal to 0:
        Let pmk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with params_cv
        If pmk is equal to 6:
            Let dst be proc components_parameters with components
            Let src be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with params_cv
            proc populate_component_category with dst, src, 1
        End If
    End If

    Let examples_cv be proc get from Dict with cmap, "examples"
    If examples_cv is not equal to 0:
        Let emk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with examples_cv
        If emk is equal to 6:
            Let dst be proc components_examples with components
            Let src be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with examples_cv
            proc populate_component_category with dst, src, 2
        End If
    End If

    Let rb_cv be proc get from Dict with cmap, "requestBodies"
    If rb_cv is not equal to 0:
        Let rbk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with rb_cv
        If rbk is equal to 6:
            Let dst be proc components_request_bodies with components
            Let src be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with rb_cv
            proc populate_component_category with dst, src, 2
        End If
    End If

    Let headers_cv be proc get from Dict with cmap, "headers"
    If headers_cv is not equal to 0:
        Let hmk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with headers_cv
        If hmk is equal to 6:
            Let dst be proc components_headers with components
            Let src be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with headers_cv
            proc populate_component_category with dst, src, 1
        End If
    End If

    Let ss_cv be proc get from Dict with cmap, "securitySchemes"
    If ss_cv is not equal to 0:
        Let ssk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with ss_cv
        If ssk is equal to 6:
            Let dst be proc components_security_schemes with components
            Let src be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with ss_cv
            proc populate_component_category with dst, src, 2
        End If
    End If

    Let links_cv be proc get from Dict with cmap, "links"
    If links_cv is not equal to 0:
        Let lnk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with links_cv
        If lnk is equal to 6:
            Let dst be proc components_links with components
            Let src be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with links_cv
            proc populate_component_category with dst, src, 2
        End If
    End If

    Let cb_cv be proc get from Dict with cmap, "callbacks"
    If cb_cv is not equal to 0:
        Let cbk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with cb_cv
        If cbk is equal to 6:
            Let dst be proc components_callbacks with components
            Let src be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with cb_cv
            proc populate_component_category with dst, src, 2
        End If
    End If

    Let pi_cv be proc get from Dict with cmap, "pathItems"
    If pi_cv is not equal to 0:
        Let pimk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with pi_cv
        If pimk is equal to 6:
            Let dst be proc components_path_items with components
            Let src be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with pi_cv
            proc populate_component_category with dst, src, 3
        End If
    End If

    proc openapi_spec_set_components with spec, components
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: PARSE
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Parse a JSON-encoded OpenAPI 3.1 document into an OpenApiSpec. (Callers
holding YAML feed it through the YAML-to-JSON converter first.)
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Parse the JSON into a ConfigValue. Read top-level "openapi" and "info"
fields. Walk "paths" mapping each URL key to a PathItem with the listed
HTTP verb operations. Each operation's "parameters" and "responses"
become Parameter records and SchemaNode bodies.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over the document.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on parse failure or schema mismatch.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "openapi_parse" takes json_text as Integer returns Integer:
    If json_text is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cv be proc json_to_config_value from JsonSchema with json_text
    If cv is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let spec be proc openapi_from_cv with cv
    proc config_value_destroy from Cfg with cv
    Return spec
End Process

@Reasoning
Convert a ConfigValue tree (the JSON parse result) into an OpenApiSpec.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Verify top-level is a map. Read openapi version. Read info { title,
version }. Walk paths.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on type mismatch.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "openapi_from_cv" takes cv as Integer returns Integer:
    If cv is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let vk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with cv
    If vk is not equal to 6:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let root be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with cv
    Let ver_cv be proc get from Dict with root, "openapi"
    If ver_cv is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let vkk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with ver_cv
    If vkk is not equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ver_str be proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with ver_cv

    Let info_cv be proc get from Dict with root, "info"
    If info_cv is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ikk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with info_cv
    If ikk is not equal to 6:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let info_map be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with info_cv
    Let title_cv be proc get from Dict with info_map, "title"
    Let ivers_cv be proc get from Dict with info_map, "version"
    If title_cv is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If ivers_cv is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let title_s be proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with title_cv
    Let ivers_s be proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with ivers_cv
    Let info be proc info_create with title_s, ivers_s
    If info is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc populate_info_extras with info, info_map
    Let spec be proc openapi_spec_create with ver_str, info
    If spec is equal to 0:
        proc info_destroy with info
        Return 0
    End If

    Let servers_cv be proc get from Dict with root, "servers"
    If servers_cv is not equal to 0:
        Let sk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with servers_cv
        If sk is equal to 5:
            Let slst be proc config_value_as_list from Cfg with servers_cv
            Let sc be proc list_length from List with slst
            Let si be 0
            While si is less than sc:
                Let entry be proc list_get from List with slst, si
                Let ek be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with entry
                If ek is equal to 6:
                    Let emap be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with entry
                    Let url_cv be proc get from Dict with emap, "url"
                    If url_cv is not equal to 0:
                        Let uk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with url_cv
                        If uk is equal to 1:
                            Let urls be proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with url_cv
                            proc openapi_spec_add_server with spec, urls
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
                Set si to si plus 1
            End While
        End If
    End If

    Let paths_cv be proc get from Dict with root, "paths"
    If paths_cv is not equal to 0:
        Let pk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with paths_cv
        If pk is equal to 6:
            Let pmap be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with paths_cv
            Let pkeys be proc keys from Dict with pmap
            Let pc be proc list_length from List with pkeys
            Let pi be 0
            While pi is less than pc:
                Let pkey be proc list_get from List with pkeys, pi
                Let pval be proc get from Dict with pmap, pkey
                Let path_item be proc path_item_from_cv with pval
                If path_item is not equal to 0:
                    proc openapi_spec_add_path with spec, pkey, path_item
                End If
                Set pi to pi plus 1
            End While
            proc list_destroy from List with pkeys
        End If
    End If

    proc populate_top_level_components with spec, root
    proc populate_top_level_security with spec, root
    proc populate_top_level_tags with spec, root
    proc populate_top_level_external_docs with spec, root

    Return spec
End Process

@Reasoning
Translate a single path-item ConfigValue (CV_MAP) into a PathItem record.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate a new PathItem. For each HTTP verb key present in the map,
build an Operation and attach to the slot.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(k) where k is the number of operations on this path.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null or non-map input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "path_item_from_cv" takes cv as Integer returns Integer:
    If cv is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let vk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with cv
    If vk is not equal to 6:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let pi be proc path_item_create
    If pi is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let map be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with cv
    proc set_operation_for_verb with pi, map, VERB_GET, "get"
    proc set_operation_for_verb with pi, map, VERB_PUT, "put"
    proc set_operation_for_verb with pi, map, VERB_POST, "post"
    proc set_operation_for_verb with pi, map, VERB_DELETE, "delete"
    proc set_operation_for_verb with pi, map, VERB_OPTIONS, "options"
    proc set_operation_for_verb with pi, map, VERB_HEAD, "head"
    proc set_operation_for_verb with pi, map, VERB_PATCH, "patch"
    proc set_operation_for_verb with pi, map, VERB_TRACE, "trace"
    Return pi
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper that extracts a verb operation from a path-item map and binds it
to the appropriate slot.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Look up the verb key in the map; if present, build an Operation and
attach.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) per verb.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "set_operation_for_verb" takes pi as Integer, map as Integer, verb as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    Let entry be proc get from Dict with map, key
    If entry is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let ek be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with entry
    If ek is not equal to 6:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let op_map be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with entry
    Let op be proc operation_create
    If op is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let id_cv be proc get from Dict with op_map, "operationId"
    If id_cv is not equal to 0:
        Let ik be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with id_cv
        If ik is equal to 1:
            Let id_s be proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with id_cv
            proc operation_set_id with op, id_s
        End If
    End If

    Let op_summary_s be proc cv_map_string_ref with op_map, "summary"
    If op_summary_s is not equal to 0:
        proc operation_set_summary with op, op_summary_s
    End If
    Let op_desc_s be proc cv_map_string_ref with op_map, "description"
    If op_desc_s is not equal to 0:
        proc operation_set_description with op, op_desc_s
    End If
    Let dep_cv be proc get from Dict with op_map, "deprecated"
    If dep_cv is not equal to 0:
        Let depk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with dep_cv
        If depk is equal to 4:
            Let depv be proc config_value_as_bool from Cfg with dep_cv
            proc operation_set_deprecated with op, depv
        End If
    End If
    Let op_tags_cv be proc get from Dict with op_map, "tags"
    If op_tags_cv is not equal to 0:
        Let tk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with op_tags_cv
        If tk is equal to 5:
            Let tlst be proc config_value_as_list from Cfg with op_tags_cv
            Let tn be proc list_length from List with tlst
            Let ti be 0
            While ti is less than tn:
                Let te be proc list_get from List with tlst, ti
                Let tek be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with te
                If tek is equal to 1:
                    Let t_s be proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with te
                    If t_s is not equal to 0:
                        proc operation_add_tag with op, t_s
                    End If
                End If
                Set ti to ti plus 1
            End While
        End If
    End If
    Let op_sec_cv be proc get from Dict with op_map, "security"
    If op_sec_cv is not equal to 0:
        Let osk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with op_sec_cv
        If osk is equal to 5:
            Let oslst be proc config_value_as_list from Cfg with op_sec_cv
            Let osn be proc list_length from List with oslst
            Let osi be 0
            While osi is less than osn:
                Let osr_cv be proc list_get from List with oslst, osi
                Let osr be proc extract_security_requirement with osr_cv
                If osr is not equal to 0:
                    proc operation_add_security with op, osr
                End If
                Set osi to osi plus 1
            End While
        End If
    End If
    Let rb_cv be proc get from Dict with op_map, "requestBody"
    If rb_cv is not equal to 0:
        Let rbk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with rb_cv
        If rbk is equal to 6:
            Let rb_clone be proc cv_deep_clone with rb_cv
            If rb_clone is not equal to 0:
                proc operation_set_request_body with op, rb_clone
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Let params_cv be proc get from Dict with op_map, "parameters"
    If params_cv is not equal to 0:
        Let pk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with params_cv
        If pk is equal to 5:
            Let plst be proc config_value_as_list from Cfg with params_cv
            Let pc be proc list_length from List with plst
            Let pi2 be 0
            While pi2 is less than pc:
                Let pe be proc list_get from List with plst, pi2
                Let pek be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with pe
                If pek is equal to 6:
                    Let pmap be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with pe
                    Let nm_cv be proc get from Dict with pmap, "name"
                    Let in_cv be proc get from Dict with pmap, "in"
                    Let sch_cv be proc get from Dict with pmap, "schema"
                    Let req_cv be proc get from Dict with pmap, "required"
                    If nm_cv is not equal to 0:
                        If in_cv is not equal to 0:
                            Let nmk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with nm_cv
                            Let ink be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with in_cv
                            If nmk is equal to 1:
                                If ink is equal to 1:
                                    Let nm_s be proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with nm_cv
                                    Let in_s be proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with in_cv
                                    Let loc be proc in_name_to_constant with in_s
                                    Let psch be 0
                                    If sch_cv is not equal to 0:
                                        Set psch to proc cv_to_schema from JsonSchema with sch_cv
                                    End If
                                    Let req_flag be 0
                                    If req_cv is not equal to 0:
                                        Let rk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with req_cv
                                        If rk is equal to 4:
                                            Set req_flag to proc config_value_as_bool from Cfg with req_cv
                                        End If
                                    End If
                                    Let param be proc parameter_create with nm_s, loc, psch, req_flag
                                    If param is not equal to 0:
                                        Let pdesc_s be proc cv_map_string_ref with pmap, "description"
                                        If pdesc_s is not equal to 0:
                                            proc parameter_set_description with param, pdesc_s
                                        End If
                                        proc operation_add_parameter with op, param
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
                Set pi2 to pi2 plus 1
            End While
        End If
    End If
    Let resp_cv be proc get from Dict with op_map, "responses"
    If resp_cv is not equal to 0:
        Let rk2 be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with resp_cv
        If rk2 is equal to 6:
            Let rmap be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with resp_cv
            Let rkeys be proc keys from Dict with rmap
            Let rc be proc list_length from List with rkeys
            Let ri be 0
            While ri is less than rc:
                Let status be proc list_get from List with rkeys, ri
                Let rval be proc get from Dict with rmap, status
                Let rsch be proc cv_to_schema from JsonSchema with rval
                If rsch is not equal to 0:
                    proc operation_add_response with op, status, rsch
                End If
                Set ri to ri plus 1
            End While
            proc list_destroy from List with rkeys
        End If
    End If
    proc path_item_set_operation with pi, verb, op
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Translate an "in" parameter location name into the IN_* constant.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Compare against "query", "header", "path", "cookie".
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns IN_QUERY (default) on unknown.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "in_name_to_constant" takes name as Integer returns Integer:
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return IN_QUERY
    End If
    Let m1 be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "query"
    If m1 is equal to 1:
        Return IN_QUERY
    End If
    Let m2 be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "header"
    If m2 is equal to 1:
        Return IN_HEADER
    End If
    Let m3 be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "path"
    If m3 is equal to 1:
        Return IN_PATH
    End If
    Let m4 be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "cookie"
    If m4 is equal to 1:
        Return IN_COOKIE
    End If
    Return IN_QUERY
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: VALIDATE
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Validate an OpenApiSpec for internal consistency. Returns a List of
ValidationIssue diagnostics. Empty list = valid. The validation
specifically checks:
  - openapi version present and starts with "3.1"
  - info.title and info.version present
  - every path begins with '/'
  - every operation has at least one declared response
  - parameter "in" values fall in {query,header,path,cookie}
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk the spec collecting issues into a fresh list. Each violation
includes a JSON-pointer-style path.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "openapi_validate" takes spec as Integer returns Integer:
    If spec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let issues be proc list_create from List
    If issues is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ver be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with spec, 0
    If ver is equal to 0:
        proc issues_append from Schema with issues, "/openapi", "missing openapi version", 1
    Otherwise:
        Let starts_31 be proc string_starts_with from StringCore with ver, "3.1"
        If starts_31 is equal to 0:
            proc issues_append from Schema with issues, "/openapi", "openapi version must begin with 3.1", 1
        End If
    End If
    Let info be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with spec, 8
    If info is equal to 0:
        proc issues_append from Schema with issues, "/info", "missing info section", 9
    End If
    Let paths be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with spec, 24
    If paths is not equal to 0:
        Let pkeys be proc keys from Dict with paths
        If pkeys is not equal to 0:
            Let pc be proc list_length from List with pkeys
            Let i be 0
            While i is less than pc:
                Let key be proc list_get from List with pkeys, i
                If key is not equal to 0:
                    Let first_ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with key, 0
                    If first_ch is not equal to 47:
                        proc issues_append from Schema with issues, key, "path key must begin with '/'", 1
                    End If
                    Let path_item be proc get from Dict with paths, key
                    If path_item is not equal to 0:
                        Let v be 1
                        While v is less than 9:
                            Let op be proc path_item_get_operation with path_item, v
                            If op is not equal to 0:
                                Let resp_dict be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with op, 24
                                Let rcount be 0
                                If resp_dict is not equal to 0:
                                    Set rcount to proc size from Dict with resp_dict
                                End If
                                If rcount is equal to 0:
                                    proc issues_append from Schema with issues, key, "operation has no responses", 9
                                End If
                            End If
                            Set v to v plus 1
                        End While
                    End If
                End If
                Set i to i plus 1
            End While
            proc list_destroy from List with pkeys
        End If
    End If
    Return issues
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CLIENT STUB GENERATION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Emit a Runa client stub for an OpenAPI spec. The output is a string of
Runa source containing one Process per Operation whose operationId is
defined. Each process signature reflects the path/query parameters as
arguments and returns Integer (a Schema-typed response handle). The
generated code references a placeholder "http_request" function expected
in the caller's runtime; it is not bound by this module.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk the paths dict in iteration order. For every operation with an id,
emit:
  Process called "<op_id>" that takes <params...> returns Integer:
      Return proc http_request with "<verb>", "<url-template>", ...
  End Process
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over operations.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure or null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "openapi_to_typed_client_stub" takes spec as Integer returns Integer:
    If spec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sb be proc stringbuilder_create from SB
    If sb is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "Note: OpenAPI client stub generated from spec\n"
    Let paths be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with spec, 24
    If paths is not equal to 0:
        Let pkeys be proc keys from Dict with paths
        If pkeys is not equal to 0:
            Let pc be proc list_length from List with pkeys
            Let i be 0
            While i is less than pc:
                Let path_key be proc list_get from List with pkeys, i
                Let path_item be proc get from Dict with paths, path_key
                If path_item is not equal to 0:
                    Let v be 1
                    While v is less than 9:
                        Let op be proc path_item_get_operation with path_item, v
                        If op is not equal to 0:
                            Let op_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with op, 0
                            If op_id is not equal to 0:
                                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "\nProcess called \""
                                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, op_id
                                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "\" returns Integer:\n    Return proc http_request with \""
                                proc verb_name_into with sb, v
                                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "\", \""
                                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, path_key
                                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "\"\nEnd Process\n"
                            End If
                        End If
                        Set v to v plus 1
                    End While
                End If
                Set i to i plus 1
            End While
            proc list_destroy from List with pkeys
        End If
    End If
    Let out be proc stringbuilder_to_string from SB with sb
    proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
    Return out
End Process

@Reasoning
Append the HTTP verb name corresponding to a VERB_* constant.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Linear switch.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "verb_name_into" takes sb as Integer, verb as Integer returns Integer:
    If verb is equal to VERB_GET:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "GET"
        Return 1
    End If
    If verb is equal to VERB_PUT:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "PUT"
        Return 1
    End If
    If verb is equal to VERB_POST:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "POST"
        Return 1
    End If
    If verb is equal to VERB_DELETE:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "DELETE"
        Return 1
    End If
    If verb is equal to VERB_OPTIONS:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "OPTIONS"
        Return 1
    End If
    If verb is equal to VERB_HEAD:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "HEAD"
        Return 1
    End If
    If verb is equal to VERB_PATCH:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "PATCH"
        Return 1
    End If
    If verb is equal to VERB_TRACE:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "TRACE"
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 1
End Process
